column4: <content>49. Hochzeitstanz im Innern eines Hauses. My N° 95.</content>

<parts.title>Ad [Addendum] 95. Witt Library. Bruegel Interior (box 5) see also P.B.II. Indoor Wedding: 1) [Notitie FG: 'best] Johnson Philadelphia, N° 420, as P.B.I. Best version to be reproduced good photograph, 311/2 x 42 in. 18[?]2 in coll. M. Roeck, Brussels, the M.E. Coninck, Brusslers, M. Menke, Antwerp; 2) Pommersfelden, photo, Eiche 75 x 105 cm; 3) Sale, Am.Art Assoc. New York, 7-I-1927, N° 50 (from the Rudolph Kann Coll.), Panel 291/2 x 42 in. signed bottom left Brveghel, 1544 (sic!); [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. This grotesque composition not by P.B.I, but probably the invention of P.B.II, partly based on P.B.; [verso] no coherence, silly repetition; 4) Meazza Sale, Milan, April 1884, N° 258, PL. 30; 5) (A XVIIth cent. variation)= actually main groups of Hermsen placed indoors: van Wijk Sale, Van Stockum, Hague, 19-VII-1943, N° 4, paneel, 39 x 51 cm.</parts.title>
